RIYADH: The minister of state for foreign affairs, Cabinet member, and climate affairs envoy, Adel Al-Jubeir, received the Belgian ambassador to the Kingdom, Dominique Mineur, in Riyadh on Monday. Mineur made her farewell to Al-Jubeir to mark the end of her tenure as her countryâ€™s ambassador to the Kingdom. The minister said that he valued the good efforts made by ambassador Mineur in strengthening ties between the two countries, wishing her every success. The meeting was attended by the director-general of the office of the minister of state for foreign affairs, Khaled bin Musaed Al-Anqari.